In fact, he‚Äôs too strong‚Äîeven his mightiest opponents are taken out with a single punch. Alongside Genos, his faithful disciple, Saitama performs his official hero duties as a member of the Hero Association. One day, monsters claiming to be from the Monster Association suddenly appeared, taking a child of Hero Association executive hostage. The S-class heroes gather and plan a raid on the Monster Association hideout to rescue the hostage. Meanwhile, Garou, a ‚Äúhuman monster‚Äù who was taken by the Monster Association during a battle with the heroes, awakens in the Monster Association hideout."

snippet.description:
Mutu Mae Basecha - Female Version (Alternate/Extended) Bashiruddin Miyan

üé∂ Mutu Mai Basechha (Female Version Cover) üé∂

Originally performed by Brijesh Shrestha/Samikshya Adhikari, this is my heartfelt female interpretation of the beautiful song Mutu Mai Basechha. I've added some extra verses to express a different emotional perspective‚Äîone that reflects a softer, more intimate side of the story.

‚ú® This version is not just a cover‚Äîit's a reimagined expression of love, pain, and longing from a female voice. I hope you connect with this rendition just as deeply as I did while creating it.

Girl, you know I want your love
Your love was handmade for somebody like me
Well, come on now, follow my lead
I may be crazy, don't mind me
Say, "Boy, let's not talk too much"
Grab on my waist and put that body on me
Well, come on now, follow my lead
Come, come on now, follow my lead, mm

I'm in love with the shape of you

And now my bed sheets smell like you

snippet.title: Bipul Chettri - Eh Saathi (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
'Eh Saathi' is the first release from the forthcoming album, 'Pravah'. As the title suggests, it's an ode to childhood friendships that transcends time. Almost written like a conversation piece put to music, the song embodies the notion of friendship that is something to nurture and celebrate, that you never take them for granted and its enduring nature of emphasizing loyalty, love, and the shared journey of life.

MUSIC
Bipul Chettri - Vocals, Guitars, Backing Vocals 
Pranai Gurung - Guitars
Rahul Rai - Bass
Rythem Bansal - Keys/Organ
Shantanu Sudarshan - Drums/Percussions 
Sumimardor Diengdoh, Bhushan Man Amatya, Prashansa Pandey Amatya - Backing Vocals 

Written and arranged by Bipul Chettri.
Recorded at Baa Baa Black Sheep Studios, Plug ‚ÄòN‚Äô Play Studios & Project Studio Productions.
Recording Engineers - Jonty Indra, Anindo Bose, Binaya Man Amatya 
Mixed & Mastered by Binaya Man Amatya

Producer - Bipul Chettri
Executive Producer - Sonam Tashi

en.title: Bipul Chettri - Eh Saathi (Official Music Video)
en.description:
'Eh Saathi' is the first release from the forthcoming album, 'Pravah'. As the title suggests, it's an ode to childhood friendships that transcends time. Almost written like a conversation piece put to music, the song embodies the notion of friendship that is something to nurture and celebrate, that you never take them for granted and its enduring nature of emphasizing loyalty, love, and the shared journey of life.

MUSIC
Bipul Chettri - Vocals, Guitars, Backing Vocals 
Pranai Gurung - Guitars
Rahul Rai - Bass
Rythem Bansal - Keys/Organ
Shantanu Sudarshan - Drums/Percussions 
Sumimardor Diengdoh, Bhushan Man Amatya, Prashansa Pandey Amatya - Backing Vocals 

Written and arranged by Bipul Chettri.
Recorded at Baa Baa Black Sheep Studios, Plug ‚ÄòN‚Äô Play Studios & Project Studio Productions.
Recording Engineers - Jonty Indra, Anindo Bose, Binaya Man Amatya 
Mixed & Mastered by Binaya Man Amatya
Album Cover Design - Manohar Rai
Album Cover Photography - Praveen Chettri
Producer - Bipul Chettri
Executive Producer - Sonam Tashi 

VIDEO
Directed by Dishant Pradhan
Director of Photography: Vashistha Pradhan 
Chief Assistant Director: Sujan Lamjel
Edited by: Dishant & Vazzu
Art Director: Tejistha Pradhan
Costume Designer: Pfulmaya
Assistant Costume Designer: Subeksha Gurung 
Assistant Cinematographer: Akash Pradhan 
Production House: Lasta Studio 
Assistant Production Manager: Nuhang Subba 
Colorist: Shiny Syko
Lead Cast: Rahul N Mukhia, Kewal Subba, Tenzein Choden

Though poles apart in their lives, beliefs and backgrounds, Vaani and Krish are perfect with each other and for each other. Will they understand that truth despite their age, their problems? 

They say flawed, imperfect people make for a perfect love story‚Ä¶and Saiyaara is about celebrating that one love story that is so deep, so pure and so caring that it is absolutely unconditional.

Vaani and Krish will have to navigate life, their problems, their insecurities to hopefully realise that only love can be the answer to everything. Saiyaara is a film that celebrates every season of love through the eyes of Vaani & Krish and poses a simple question‚Ä¶do you love someone so much that you would bet everything to keep that person in your life?
